{
  "stem": "7598.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went to stay with my uncle and aunt.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This, this-- I will speak to you in one moment, I just wanted to fill in something.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We saw loads of prisoners of war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Oh, I forgot to say that geographically, it may be interesting to someone, we were caught by the Germans between Amiens and Arras on the way to Paris.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We must have crossed the frontier somewhere south of Calais or Bologna, but even I don't know exactly where it was.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we were caught by the German near Arras.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we saw loads of prisoners of war being marched along by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I'm always horrified when I see how well the British treated the German prisoners of war compared to what I saw happening there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We went into a shop, and we bought some cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we didn't have that many cigarettes, so we stood by these prisoners of war who were limping along tired and, you know, with a defeated attitude.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we said Shalom.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And whoever understood it, we gave cigarettes to.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We weren't discriminating, but we only had a few, and we knew the Germans weren't going to treat them very well.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In fact, they were beating them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They really were not treating the prisoners at all well, not according to the Geneva conference anyway.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And my little grandson likes this little story.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
